  <div class="pagehead">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / Shipping &amp; Returns</div>
      <h1>Shipping &amp; Returns</h1>
      <p>How we pack, ship, and stand behind every piece.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="prose">
    <h2>How we pack</h2>
    <p>Minerals and fossils are wrapped by hand, cushioned, and double boxed for anything fragile or high value. Crystal points and delicate clusters get extra care around the terminations. Lava lamps ship in their own reinforced packaging with the liquid element secured.</p>
    <h2>Shipping</h2>
    <p>We ship within the United States, insured, with tracking on every order. Shipping is calculated at checkout, and orders over a set amount ship free. Most orders go out within a few business days. If a piece needs special handling or freight, we will reach out before shipping.</p>
    <h2>Returns</h2>
    <p>If a specimen arrives damaged in transit, contact us right away with photos and we will make it right. Because every piece is one of a kind and described honestly with its condition, we ask that you read the listing and reach out with any questions before you buy. If a piece is not as described, we will accept a return.</p>
    <h2>Local pickup at the 127</h2>
    <p>During the Highway 127 Yard Sale, August 6 through 9, 2026, you can buy and carry pieces home in person. No shipping needed. Come find us on US-127 in Grimsley, between the Dollar General and Taco Bros.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:26px;"><a class="btn btn-dark" href="/contact">Ask a shipping question</a></p>
  </div>
</Base>
